d the action be labeled as \\\"advisory_preparation\\\" since we want a deterministic setup? Maybe the agent guidance is optional or could provide info on system properties, but no environment settings are needed. I need to finalize the dependencies list.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating library compatibility**\\n\\nI'm considering whether there could be an issue with adding the jsr311-api. I realize that the Jersey-core jar already contains the javax/ws/rs classes, so that shouldn't be a problem. It looks like everything should work well together. I’ll have to double-check if there are any dependencies or conflicts, but at the moment, this seems like a straightforward integration!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_20ZO1RVLi3ZAtkJ3GgDRY9EU|fc_092998252523d593016a43095b58b88193b3919b7f89f97fe4", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nprint(urllib.request.urlopen('https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/javax/mail/mail/1.4/mail-1.4.pom', timeout=20).read().decode()[:2000])\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1062, "output": 1581, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21075, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782778175040, "responseId": "resp_092998252523d593016a43093f63ac8193b8bf6e482dbad18d"}}
