ct valid JSON with the right entries.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Identifying risks in OSGi setup**\\n\\nI’m concerned about the risk of having \\\"old org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0\\\" on the classpath. If it remains there, it can duplicate OSGi classes and obscure the 4.2 API. It's crucial to replace it in the generated or fixed build files to avoid this issue. However, I recognize that the deterministic setup cannot represent the removal of that old version completely. I wonder if I should explicitly include this risk in my documentation.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Jersey core 1.14 declares several runtime APIs as Maven provided dependencies. Meaningful tests that exercise its JAXB, JavaMail/MIME, or OSGi support need those APIs on the test classpath; the current failure is specifically because Jersey 1.14 moved to OSGi Core 4.2.0, which provides org.osgi.framework.BundleReference while the old osgi_R4_core 1.0 does not.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.osgi:org.osgi.core:4.2.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"jersey-core 1.14 declares this as a provided dependency, and its OsgiRegistry/Activator code references org.osgi.framework.BundleReference, which is absent from org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.mail:mail:1.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"jersey-core 1.14 declares JavaMail as provided and contains MIME/DataSource providers that reference javax.mail and javax.activation APIs not present in modern JDKs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.xml.bind:jaxb-api:2.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"jersey-core 1.14 declares JAXB as provided and contains XML/JAXB provider classes that reference javax.xml.bind APIs not present in modern JDKs.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, environment variable, or system property appears necessary. If exercising OSGi support, use an in-test minimal/mock BundleContext rather than requiring an external OSGi container.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If the obsolete org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0 dependency remains on the classpath alongside org.osgi.core 4.2.0, duplicate OSGi classes may make behavior classpath-order dependent; local Gradle and Native Image verification should confirm the final build file.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_092998252523d593016a430968c5848193b2cbdbbcb221f920\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 7014, "output": 986, "cacheRead": 14336, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22336, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782778203786, "responseId": "resp_092998252523d593016a43095c3f0c8193b46221ac739c9ad0"}, "toolResults": []}
